# BFS Traversal (Undirected Graph)

## Problem
Perform Breadth-First Search starting from node 1.

## Input
- n nodes
- adjacency list

## Output
- BFS traversal order

## Time Complexity
O(N + M)

## Space Complexity
O(N)
class BeingZero {
    public List<Integer> solve(int n, List<List<Integer>> AdjList) {
        List<Integer> ans = new ArrayList<>();
        Queue<Integer> q = new LinkedList<>();
        boolean[] visited = new boolean[n + 1];

        q.add(1);
        visited[1] = true;

        while (!q.isEmpty()) {
            int u = q.poll();
            ans.add(u);

            for (int v : AdjList.get(u)) {
                if (!visited[v]) {
                    visited[v] = true;
                    q.add(v);
                }
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
}
